Shown on the x-axis is the average number of years of schooling of women in the reproductive age (15 to 49 years).
On the y-axis you find the 'total fertility rate' – the number of live births per woman in reproductive age.
Average years of schooling of women in reproductive age
Source: United Nations – Population Division (2022); Our World In Data (2017)
